	<p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs8498B7A6">WEST VIRGINIA LEGISLATURE</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 </span><span class="csC2FEE544">REGULAR SESSION</span><div style="width:49pt;height:32pt;border-width:0.5pt;border-style:solid;border-color:Black;background-color:#FFFFFF;margin:0pt 9pt 0pt 9pt;padding:5pt 0pt 0pt 0pt;">
		<p class="csAC81313F"><span class="csB9803513">FISCAL NOTE</span></p></div>
	</p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Introduced</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">Senate Bill 761</span></p><p class="csFF933113"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Senators Hamilton, Barnhart, Deeds, Garcia, Hart, Morris, Thorne, and Woodrum</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Introduced February 5, 2026; referred<br/>to the Committee on Natural Resources; and then to the Committee on Finance]</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, by adding a new article, designated &sect;5B-12-1, &sect;5B-12-2, &sect;5B-12-3, &sect;5B-12-4, &sect;5B-12-5, &sect;5B-12-6, &sect;5B-12-7, and &sect;5B-12-8, relating to in-state production of value-added forest products; providing a purpose; providing definitions; establishing how tax credits are applied; clarifying eligibility and compliance standards; clarifying rule-making authority; and creating civil penalties. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs456817A0">Article 12. IN-STATE PROCESSING INCENTIVE FOR NON-ROUNDWOOD FOREST PRODUCTS.</span></h2>
	<h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">&nbsp;</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;5B-12-1. Purpose.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">The purpose of this article is to encourage the in-state production of value-added forest products by providing tax credits to manufacturers that materially transform West Virginia harvested roundwood into qualified non-roundwood products. The credit may be applied to corporate net income tax or to personal income tax for owners of pass-through entities. </span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">&nbsp;</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;5B-12-2. Definitions.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">As used in this article:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">&quot;Expansion&quot; means a measurable increase in annual production capacity or a new production line that processes West Virginia sourced wood into qualified non-roundwood products.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">&quot;Green ton&quot; means one ton of freshly harvested wood with natural moisture content.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">&quot;Ineligible activities&quot; include debarking, sorting, cutting to length, trimming stems, bundling, loading, unloading, exporting raw logs or stems, and chipping solely to create transport length.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">&quot;Interim conversion factor&quot; means 1MBF (Doyle) which is equivalent to seven green tons of mixed Appalachian hardwood logs.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">&quot;Minimum transformation standard&quot; means processing that alters the cross-sectional geometry of the wood or alters the fiber structure. Simple cutting, trimming, debarking, handling, sorting, or preparing logs or stems for transport do not meet this standard.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">&quot;Non-roundwood product&quot; means a wood product whose cross-sectional geometry or fiber structure has been materially transformed. Qualifying products include veneer, composites, laminated veneer lumber, laminated strand lumber, cross laminated timber, oriented strand board, medium density fiberboard, high density fiberboard, wood pellets, wood briquettes, industrial</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">wood chips for fiber manufacturing, and similar products.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">&quot;Pass-through entity&quot; means a business entity that is not subject to the corporate net income tax and whose income is taxed under the West Virginia personal income tax, including but not limited to partnerships, limited liability companies taxed as partnerships, S corporations, and sole proprietorships.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">&quot;West Virginia sourced feedstock&quot; means roundwood harvested within the State of West Virginia.</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">&nbsp;</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;5B-12-3. Standard incentive schedule and application of tax credit.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) Incentives provided under this article are tax credits applied either:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Against the taxpayer&rsquo;s corporate net income tax liability; or</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Against the taxpayer&rsquo;s personal income tax liability if the taxpayer is a pass-through entity or the owner of a pass-through entity.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) The credit is available only for qualified non-roundwood products manufactured in West Virginia using West Virginia sourced feedstock.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) Standard incentive schedule:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Tier 1: 0 to 140,000 green tons at $3 per ton.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Tier 2: 140,001 to 700,000 green tons at $2 per ton.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Tier 3: 700,001 green tons and above at $1.25 per ton.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) Annual cap: $1.25 million per facility per calendar year.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(e) Pro-rating: Payments shall be prorated to the manufacturer only on the West Virginia-origin share of feedstock (e.g. 80 percent West Virginia wood shall equal 80 percent of calculated credit).</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(f) The credit shall be applied to the applicable tax liability for the taxable year in which the qualified activity occurred. The credit may not reduce tax liability below zero unless refundability is authorized in a future act.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;5B-12-4. Temporary enhanced rate for new facilities and expansions; application of tax credit.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) A manufacturer that begins new operations or completes a qualifying expansion may elect a temporary enhanced tax credit for five calendar years.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Enhanced incentive schedule:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Enhanced Tier 1: 0 to 50,000 green tons at $6 per ton.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Enhanced Tier 2: 50,001 to 250,000 green tons at $4 per ton.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Enhanced Tier 3: 250,001 green tons and above at $2.50 per ton.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) Enhanced annual cap: $2.5 million per facility per calendar year.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) For an expansion, the enhanced credit applies only to the increase in annual green tons consumed above the facility&rsquo;s five-year production average preceding the expansion.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(e) All credits under the enhanced schedule shall be prorated according to the percentage of total wood purchased that is sourced from West Virginia.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(f) Credits under the enhanced schedule shall be applied either to the taxpayer&rsquo;s corporate net income tax liability or to the taxpayer&rsquo;s personal income tax liability if the taxpayer is a pass-through entity or the owner of a pass-through entity.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(g) After the five-year enhanced period, the facility shall revert to the standard incentive schedule in &sect;5B-12-3 of this code.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(h) A facility may not claim more than one enhanced expansion credit at a time. An expansion begun during an active five-year enhanced period is not eligible. After the five-year period ends, a new expansion may qualify.</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">&nbsp;</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;5B-12-5. Eligibility and claims.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) A manufacturer must produce a qualified non-roundwood product within West Virginia using West Virginia harvested forest products.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) A manufacturer shall self-report quarterly and submit scale tickets, tonnage summaries, and related documentation as required by the Division of Economic Development.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) The Division of Economic Development may conduct random audits.</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">&nbsp;</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;5B-12-6. Guardrails and compliance.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) Only material transformations which meet the minimum standard qualify for the credit.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) No credit may be issued for ineligible activities.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) The Division of Economic Development shall promulgate rules to carry out the adoption documentation and verification requirements pursuant to &sect;5B-2-2 of this code.</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">&nbsp;</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;5B-12-7. Rulemaking authority.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">The Division of Economic Development shall promulgate rules to carry out the implementation of this article pursuant to &sect;5B-2-2 of this code. </span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">&nbsp;</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;5B-12-8. Penalties for falsification, misrepresentation, and improper claims.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) A manufacturer that knowingly falsifies records, submits inaccurate scale tickets or tonnage summaries, misrepresents the percentage of West Virginia sourced wood, or submits claims for ineligible timber or ineligible activities is subject to the penalties in this section.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Any tax credit improperly received shall be repaid at 200 percent of the credit issued and interest shall be paid at market rate from the date the improper credit was issued until repayment is made in full.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) The Division of Economic Development may assess a civil penalty, suspend eligibility for future credits, or permanently bar a manufacturer from participating if the violation is intentional.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) The Attorney General may bring a civil action to recover repayment, penalties, and interest.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(e) Nothing in this section prevents criminal prosecution where fraud is involved.</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to provide tax credits to encourage in-state production of value-added forest products.</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added.</span></p>


